Quality Material, DIY available Premium flexible and durable neoprene material allows bundling up multiple cables without tearing. Easy DIY customization, cut holes into sleeves at any position to allow cables to be separated.

Easy installation Easy to use, just gather cables together, wrap the sleeve around and zip-up, ideal for home and office use.

reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a beige option to hide a bundle of cords. I was concerned about how many I could fit... the material is stretchy and I fit at least 6 in one section. The zipper feels fairly stable, too. Good stuff.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Clean and easy to use. Significant visual results
reviews.reviewText: I used this to contain a mess of power cables and coming off the back of my desk. The stretchy material this is made from allowed me to bundle up excess wiring and tuck it all in to the fabric tube. The zipper is of sufficient quality that when I over-stuffed the wrap it worked just fine.If you're going to be swapping cables every once in a while this is probably not the right solution; velcro ties would work better. But this really does a nice job hiding and containing excess wire.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Wish these were longer.
reviews.reviewText: I enjoyed using these for some light cable management under my desk. They work great for their size and can be modified to split out cables. My biggest issue is that the sleeves always seem a bit short and three to four thicker cables will easily fill this sleeve to the brim making smaller cables harder to adjust. I love the ease of use and removal of balls of cables but will be looking for larger variants of this item for future purchases.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars This product reminded me of why I use buttons on my jackets
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased a standing desk, and as such I was bewildered when I saw the entangled disaster that was now clearly revealed behind my desk. I had seen some videos where individuals velcroed their power cables beneath the top of their desk, and then routed the cables through sleeves in such an organized fashion. These sleeves accomplish this quite well, reducing the clutter considerably.In the product picture, the sleeves appear almost foam-like, with a supposed plushy springiness to them. However, this is not at all the case. The material is a strong neoprene that does stretch quite a bit - enough where I could get nearly 8 cables into one (albeit, not without some intense finagling). Some reviewers expressed dissatisfaction with the fixed lengths; I was able to shorten some, but with the reasonable side effect of bulging.The weakness with this product is simply that it relies on technology from the 1920s. Zipper are so infuriating, always ceasing to properly be zipped (or unzipped!). Of the four sleeves that I received, one zipper in particular was damaged, and I spent at least 45 minutes trying to get the thing to operate. When at last it did, I actually routed my cables through the looped enclosure, rather than wrapping the sleeve around the cables (as expected) so I didn't have to unzip and rezip it again.For those of you eyeing this product - if you have ever expressed frustration with a zipper before, do yourself a favor and buy Velcro sleeves to avoid any possible headaches down the road.
